We sequenced 189 tumours, of which 43 had matching normal tissue also sequenced on the Nanopore.

QC dot plots

Textual Summary

Primary sequencing results are summarized in Figure 1.d. Sequencing yielded a median of 17.5-fold coverage for normal samples and 26-fold for the tumours. Reads were relatively long, with a median N50 of 31.3 kbp, and the longest read across this data set reaching 1036455bp. 77.8% of yield derived from reads greater than 20Kb in length. Base error (edit distance of aligned reads to the GRCh38 reference) was 4%. This is similar to other runs on this chemistry. Chimeric artifacts were present in a median of 4.1% of reads, also similar to other runs with this sequencing chemistry. There was no evidence of microbial contamination in any of the samples, wtih a median of 97.8% of reads matching GRCh38, and less than 0.2% of reads matching microbial taxa in any sample.

Approximate fold coverage per sample sequenced, with medians of just below 17.5X for normals, and 26X for tumours. Per-flowcell quality control statistics. A median yield of 68.4 Gbp per flowcell was observed, with 77.8% of that yield from reads greater than 20Kb in length. The median read N50 was 31.3kbp. Base error (edit distance to reference) was 4%, similar to other runs on this chemistry. We assessed chimeric artifacts, which were present in a median of 4.1% of reads. By BBT, a median of 97.8% of reads matched the human reference, while no sample showed more than 0.2% of reads matching microbial taxa.
